article.description: The Atlanta Hawks started hot.  The  Washington Wizards finished cold.
article.headline: Hawks built big first-quarter lead
article.linkText: Arenas no help as Wizards fall to Hawks
article.story:
WASHINGTON (Ticker) -- The Atlanta Hawks started hot.  The 
Washington Wizards finished cold.

Shareef Abdur-Rahim had 25 points and 12 rebounds as the Hawks
capitalized on a big first quarter en route to an 83-73 victory
over the Wizards.

Playing the opener of a six-game road trip, the Hawks made 12 of
their first 13 shots and built a 29-7 lead less than nine
minutes into the contest.

Abdur-Rahim scored 16 points and Stephen Jackson and Jason Terry
each had 10 in the first half as the Hawks settled for a 54-43
advantage.

Washington got back in the game, pulling within 65-60 after
three quarters. But the Wizards went over 6 1/2 minutes without
a basket to start the fourth quarter, making just 3-of-17 shots
in the final period.

The Wizards welcomed back guard Gilbert Arenas, who had missed
the last six games and 14 of the last 15 with an abdominal
injury.  But Arenas struggled as he missed 14 of his first 17
shots, finishing with 14 points on 5-of-19 shooting.
